  "prompt": "What are some good psychological thriller movies of 2015?",
  "response": "2015 saw the release of several engaging psychological thrillers that captivated audiences. Here are some notable films from that year:\n\n1. **\"Ex Machina\"** - Directed by Alex Garland, this film explores the complexities of artificial intelligence through a tense narrative involving a young programmer who is selected to evaluate the capabilities and consciousness of a highly advanced humanoid A.I.\n\n2. **\"The Gift\"** - Directed by Joel Edgerton, this movie follows a married couple whose lives are thrown into a tailspin after a series of encounters with an old acquaintance, unraveling a gripping tale of secrets and past wrongdoings.\n\n3. **\"Room\"** - While it is more of a drama, \"Room\" contains psychological elements that delve deeply into the mental states of its characters. Directed by Lenny Abrahamson and based on the novel by Emma Donoghue, it focuses on a woman and her young son held captive in a small room and their subsequent adjustment to the outside world.\n\n4. **\"The Invitation\"** - Directed by Karyn Kusama, this film is a suspenseful tale about a man who attends a dinner party at his former home and gradually becomes convinced that the host and their new group of friends have sinister intentions.\n\n5. **\"Anomalisa\"** - Directed by Charlie Kaufman and Duke Johnson, this stop-motion animated film uses its unique visual style to tell a deeply psychological story about a man isolated by his own perceptions, questioning the nature of reality and personal connections.\n\nThese films offer a range of thought-provoking narratives and are well-regarded for their psychological depth and thrilling elements.",
